mousedirlist - click a directory from dirlist output

Description:
Run 'dirlist' first to show files and directories on screen, then run 'mousedirlist'. The program overlays an inverted mouse cursor on the existing screen. Left-click a blue directory name to print its contents below (same format as 'dirlist'). Right-click to exit without listing.

Only names from the remembered 'dirlist' directory are clickable on screen (UTF/garbage text is ignored). The absolute listing path is stored independently of 'dirchange'.

Clicking a file, empty space, or anything that is not a blue directory name prints an error and exits. Right-click exits without action.

Usage:
mousedirlist [<directory_path>]

Examples:
dirlist
mousedirlist

dirlist programs
mousedirlist

dirlist /programs/utils
mousedirlist /programs/utils
